resources to work from to one

00:09:00.510 --> 00:09:01.910
or the other world.

00:09:01.910 --> 00:09:04.730
Android tends to run in what's
known as the normal world, and

00:09:04.730 --> 00:09:07.300
things like secure bootloaders
and stuff tend to run in

00:09:07.300 --> 00:09:07.910
secure worlds.

00:09:07.910 --> 00:09:10.100
It tends not to be something
that will be useful from an

00:09:10.100 --> 00:09:12.760
application in Android.

00:09:12.760 --> 00:09:16.740
It's more designed at hardware
manufacturers to use.

